[5.7452, "o", "\u001b[4A\n\n\n\u001b[1;38;5;42m\u2714\u001b[0m published \"ollama-native\" \u2014 reachable privately, no public port\u001b[K\r\n\r\u001b[2K\r\u001b[?2004l\u001b[?25h\u001b[?1002l\u001b[?1003l\u001b[?1006l\r\n\u001b[38;5;39m\u2022\u001b[0m You're set. What just happened, and what's next:\r\n\u001b[38;5;241m  \u2022 This machine joined a private, encrypted mesh \u2014 no ports opened, no networking to configure.\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;241m  \u2022 Your local model is now an addressable private service other machines can reach.\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n  \u001b[38;5;245mroute traffic:\u001b[0m \u001b[38;5;252msudo -E falcon up      (brings the encrypted tunnel up)\u001b[0m\r\n  \u001b[38;5;245mcall it (from another machine on your network):\u001b[0m \u001b[38;5;252mfalcon grant llm://ollama-native  \u2192  falcon resolve ollama-native --cap <token>\u001b[0m\r\n  \u001b[38;5;245msee the mesh:\u001b[0m \u001b[38;5;252mfalcon status      \u00b7      falcon ping <peer>\u001b[0m\r\n"]
